Reports of h-tests (Correlation, t-test...)

Source: R/report.htest.R
report.htest.Rd

Create a report of an h-test object (t.test(), cor.test()).

# S3 method for htest
report(x, ...)

# S3 method for htest
report_effectsize(x, ...)

# S3 method for htest
report_table(x, ...)

# S3 method for htest
report_statistics(x, table = NULL, ...)

# S3 method for htest
report_parameters(x, table = NULL, ...)

# S3 method for htest
report_model(x, table = NULL, ...)

# S3 method for htest
report_info(x, effectsize = NULL, ...)

# S3 method for htest
report_text(x, table = NULL, ...)

Arguments

x

Object of class htest.
...

Arguments passed to or from other methods.
table

Provide the output of report_table() to avoid its re-computation.
effectsize

Provide the output of report_effectsize() to avoid its re-computation.

Value

A list-object of class report, which contains further list-objects with a short and long description of the model summary, as well as a short and long table of parameters and fit indices.

See also

Specific components of reports (especially for stats models):

  • report_table

  • report_parameters

  • report_statistics

  • report_effectsize

  • report_model

  • report_random

  • report_performance

  • report_info

  • report_text

Other types of reports:

  • report_system

  • report_packages

  • report_participants

  • report_sample

Methods:

  • as.report

Examples

report(cor.test(iris$Sepal.Width, iris$Sepal.Length, method = "spearman"))

#> Warning: Cannot compute exact p-value with ties
#> Effect sizes were labelled following Funder's (2019) recommendations.
#> 
#> The Spearman's rank correlation rho between iris$Sepal.Width and iris$Sepal.Length is negative, significant and small (rho = -0.17, S = 6.56e+05, p < .05)
report(cor.test(iris$Sepal.Width, iris$Sepal.Length, method = "pearson"))

#> Effect sizes were labelled following Funder's (2019) recommendations.
#> 
#> The Pearson's product-moment correlation between iris$Sepal.Width and iris$Sepal.Length is negative, not significant and small (r = -0.12, 95% CI [-0.27, 0.04], t(148) = -1.44, p = 0.152)
report(t.test(iris$Sepal.Width, iris$Sepal.Length))

#> Effect sizes were labelled following Cohen's (1988) recommendations.
#> 
#> The Welch Two Sample t-test testing the difference between iris$Sepal.Width and iris$Sepal.Length (mean of x = 3.06, mean of y = 5.84) suggests that the effect is negative, significant and large (difference = -2.79, 95% CI [-2.94, -2.64], t(225.68) = -36.46, p < .001; Cohen's d = -4.85, 95% CI [-5.37, -4.33])
report(t.test(iris$Sepal.Width, iris$Sepal.Length, var.equal = TRUE))

#> Effect sizes were labelled following Cohen's (1988) recommendations.
#> 
#> The Two Sample t-test testing the difference between iris$Sepal.Width and iris$Sepal.Length (mean of x = 3.06, mean of y = 5.84) suggests that the effect is negative, significant and large (difference = -2.79, 95% CI [-2.94, -2.64], t(298) = -36.46, p < .001; Cohen's d = -4.22, 95% CI [-4.63, -3.82])
report(t.test(mtcars$mpg ~ mtcars$vs))

#> Effect sizes were labelled following Cohen's (1988) recommendations.
#> 
#> The Welch Two Sample t-test testing the difference of mtcars$mpg by mtcars$vs (mean in group 0 = 16.62, mean in group 1 = 24.56) suggests that the effect is positive, significant and large (difference = 7.94, 95% CI [-11.46, -4.42], t(22.72) = -4.67, p < .001; Cohen's d = -1.96, 95% CI [-2.94, -0.95])
report(t.test(mtcars$mpg, mtcars$vs, paired=TRUE))

#> Effect sizes were labelled following Cohen's (1988) recommendations.
#> 
#> The Paired t-test testing the difference between mtcars$mpg and mtcars$vs (mean of the differences = 19.65) suggests that the effect is NA, significant and large (difference = , 95% CI [17.60, 21.71], t(31) = 19.49, p < .001; Cohen's d = 3.50, 95% CI [2.56, 4.43])
report(t.test(iris$Sepal.Width, mu = 1))

#> Effect sizes were labelled following Cohen's (1988) recommendations.
#> 
#> The One Sample t-test testing the difference between iris$Sepal.Width (mean = 3.06) and mu = 1 suggests that the effect is positive, significant and large (difference = 2.06, 95% CI [2.99, 3.13], t(149) = 57.81, p < .001; Cohen's d = 4.74, 95% CI [4.17, 5.29])
